{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018JcFD6c296Bxab8D9hoKMn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information needed. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nHere are the relevant code snippets for Pyth Hermes REST API integration and route registration:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **Hermes URL & Fetch Pattern** — `pyth-poster.ts`\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pyth-poster.ts`\n\n- **Lines 37-40**: Factory function with default Hermes endpoint\n  ```typescript\n  export function createHermesFetcher(\n    endpoint = \"https://hermes.pyth.network\",\n  ): HermesFetcher {\n    const client = new HermesClient(endpoint, {});\n  ```\n\n- **Lines 43-48**: Fetch pattern using `HermesClient`\n  ```typescript\n  async fetchLatestBtcPrice(): Promise<HermesPrice | null> {\n    try {\n      const updates = await client.getLatestPriceUpdates(\n        [BTC_USD_FEED_ID],\n        { encoding: \"base64\", parsed: true },\n      );\n  ```\n\n- **Lines 14-15**: BTC/USD feed ID constant\n  ```typescript\n  export const BTC_USD_FEED_ID =\n    \"0xe62df6c8b4a85fe1a67db44dc12de5db330f7ac66b72dc658afedf0f4a415b43\";\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## 2. **Response Parsing** — `pyth-poster.ts`\n\n**Lines 49-66**: Full response parsing with VAA extraction\n```typescript\nconst feed = updates.parsed?.[0];\nif (!feed?.price) return null;\n\nconst price = BigInt(feed.price.price);\nconst expo = feed.price.expo;\n// Compute human-readable price: price * 10^expo\nconst priceHuman = Number(price) * Math.pow(10, expo);\n\n// Extract VAA from binary data (base64-encoded)\nconst vaaBase64 = updates.binary?.data?.[0] ?? null;\n\nreturn {\n  price,\n  expo,\n  publishTime: feed.price.publish_time,\n  priceHuman,\n  vaaBase64,\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. **Caching Pattern** — `closecall-clock.ts`\n\n**Lines 95-96**: In-memory cache in the worker\n```typescript\n/** Cached latest boundary price (in-memory). */\nlet cachedBoundaryPrice: BoundaryPrice | null = null;\n```\n\n**Lines 189-221**: DB persistence (upsert into `closecall_candles` table)\n```typescript\nasync function loadLatestBoundaryFromDb(): Promise<void> {\n  try {\n    const rows = await sql<{\n      minute_ts: string;\n      price: string;\n      expo: number;\n      price_human: number;\n    }[]>`\n      SELECT minute_ts, price, expo, price_human\n      FROM closecall_candles\n      ORDER BY minute_ts DESC\n      LIMIT 1\n    `;\n    // ... sets cachedBoundaryPrice\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Lines 167-187**: Save to DB with VAA proof\n```typescript\nasync function saveBoundaryPrice(\n  minuteTs: number,\n  price: bigint,\n  expo: number,\n  priceHuman: number,\n  hermesVaa: string | null,\n): Promise<void> {\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO closecall_candles (minute_ts, price, expo, price_human, hermes_vaa)\n    VALUES (${minuteTs}, ${price.toString()}, ${expo}, ${priceHuman}, ${hermesVaa})\n    ON CONFLICT (minute_ts) DO NOTHING\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. **Route Registration** — `index.ts`\n\n**Authenticated routes** (JWT required):\n\n**Lines 83-88**: Profile routes (JWT on all methods)\n```typescript\napp.use(\n  \"/profile/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\napp.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n**Lines 90-104**: Fairness routes (JWT + rate limiting)\n```typescript\napp.use(\n  \"/fairness/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret }),\n);\napp.use(\n  \"/fairness/*\",\n  createRateLimitMiddleware({\n    perWallet: config.rateLimitPerWallet,\n    global: config.rateLimitGlobal,\n    windowMs: 60_000,\n  }),\n);\n```\n\n**Unauthed routes** (no JWT):\n\n**Lines 60-81**: Auth routes (lighter rate limiting by IP)\n```typescript\napp.use(\n  \"/auth/*\",\n  createRateLimitMiddleware({\n    perWallet: 20,\n    global: config.rateLimitGlobal,\n    windowMs: 60_000,\n  }),\n);\napp.route(\n  \"/auth\",\n  createAuthRoutes({\n    authDb,\n    jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret,\n    cluster: config.cluster,\n    challengeTtlSeconds: config.challengeTtlSeconds,\n    accessTokenTtlSeconds: config.accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n    refreshTokenTtlDays: config.refreshTokenTtlDays,\n  }),\n);\n```\n\n**Lines 179-186**: Close Call routes (unauthed, but mounted after JWT/rate limit middleware that applies to `/fairness/*`)\n```typescript\napp.route(\"/closecall\", createCloseCallRoutes({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair,\n  clockWorker: closeCallClock,\n  sql,\n}));\n```\n\n**Lines 188-189**: Rounds routes (unauthed GET)\n```typescript\napp.route(\"/fairness/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. **Close Call Routes Details** — `closecall.ts`\n\nAll routes in Close Call are unauthed (no middleware applied):\n\n- **Lines 120-156**: `GET /closecall/current-round` — fetch active round from on-chain\n- **Lines 158-163**: `GET /closecall/history` — DB query, paginated\n- **Lines 169-254**: `GET /closecall/candles` — candle pairs from `closecall_candles` table + current cached price\n- **Lines 263-372**: `POST /closecall/bet` — co-sign transaction, create/join round"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6bc187ffa3ff0d57 (use SendMessage with to: 'a6bc187ffa3ff0d57' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51925\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 28862</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abd010b6-9bf8-408c-8fec-8f2eb32c16a2","uuid":"a120147c-51e0-4634-a178-5aab56633bb2","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:58:40.174Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find how the Pyth Hermes REST API is currently fetched in the codebase, particularly in `services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`. I need to see:\n1. The Hermes URL and fetch pattern used\n2. How the response is parsed\n3. Any caching patterns\n\nAlso check `services/backend/src/index.ts` for how routes are registered (both authed and unauthed).\n\nReturn the relevant cod